Each piece is individually handmade. The process is labour intensive and starts with delicate, careful modelling. When Audrey is happy with the model a mould is made and cast. Finally, the piece is polished and finishing touches, added.  

Rynhart Fine Art Bronze sculptures was started by Jeanne Rynhart in 1981. In 1994 Audrey Rynhart, Jeanne's daughter, joined her mother and now she and her husband Les Elliot run the business from their studio in Glengarriff, West Cork.

Within the range there is something for everyone. From contemporary to traditional from small pieces to large lamps and objets d'art - a Rynhart Bronze is perfect gift for any occasion, either to mark an important event or to buy for yourself or a loved one.

name: Symbols of Ireland Bone China Mug - The Wild Goose Studio
description:
Symbols of Ireland Bone China Mug created and designed by The Wild Goose Studio, based in Kinsale, Co. Cork.

St Patrick, ireland's Patron saint, used shamrock to explain the mysteries of Christianity when he brought the new religion to these shores. St. Brendan is thought to have discovered America in the 6th century on his quest to discover the Promised land. All three represent different aspects of the Irish.

Inspire by Irelands Long history and rich heritage, we work with today's artists to create eye- catching pieces which also appeal to the heart. Drawing on mythology, symbols, stories, images and poetry, we access the richness of shared memory and show it in visual design.

Under the shadow of Benbulbin, this Cross is close to the grave of W.B Yeats. Its iconography is as complex as it is exquisite. name: Céad Míle Fáilte Plaque - The Wild Goose Studio
description:
Céad Míle Fáilte Plaque - The Wild Goose Studio

The traditional Gaelic greeting which means 100,000 welcomes. The Irish respect the significance of the welcome as a threshold or rite of passage. Among Celts, there is a wide recognition of the importance of chance meetings & random events (synchronicities) with a renowned openness to new experiences, opportunities & people.This is characterised by the expansive & generous nature of the phrase ‘céad míle fáilte’.

Each friend represents a world in us, a world possibly not born until they arrive. Anais Nin

From an original stone, carved by Tom Little

Dimensions: 20 x 13cm

name: The Life of W.B. Yeats - by Terence Brown
description:
The Life of W.B. Yeats - by Terence Brown
Published by Gill & Macmillan

"A central focus of this study is Yeat's perennial pursuit of sacral power which he saw as being vested in traditional institutions. It examines how at various stages of his life he sought to acquire this power for himself in such 'institutions' as a magical order, a nation, a theatre, the community of the dead, and climatically, an occult marriage. The concluding stages of the book assess Yeat's final years as a crisis of that faith in institutions, which had hitherto sustained him in all he attempted."--BOOK JACKET
